<p>In a video discussing social media with ex-social media employees, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tPsOYuuwybA">Anthony Padilla</a> (2020) reflects on the noticeable changes in social media algorithms.</p>

<p>He highlights that <b>the algorithm now focuses on showing us content that we spend the most time on, rather than quality content we actually like.</b></p>

<p>Social media does not foster authentic and genuine content. With how easy it is to produce AI-generated content, finding authenticity becomes harder than ever before. </p>

<p>AI Instagram influencers are already becoming a thing (<a href="https://www.businessinsider.com/ai-already-replacing-instagram-influencers-jobs-2023-12">Business Insider</a>, 2023)...</p>
